The paper deals with the Lovasz Local Lemma, which is a fundamental tool in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The paper discusses the algorithmic aspects of the lemma and presents a new approach to derandomizing it. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and graph theory (cs.GT) to some extent, which makes these sub-categories less likely but still possible.
